## 🛠️ How to Setup Locally

> This is a static web-based project. You don’t need a server to run it unless you plan to connect it with a backend.

### ✅ Option 1: Run with VS Code

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/shreeja1128/ride-managment-system.git
   cd ride-managment-system

ride-managment-system/
│
├── index.html                    # Home page
├── driverLogin.html             # Driver login
├── driverDashboard.html         # Driver profile page
├── passengerLogin.html          # Passenger login
├── registerDriver.html          # Driver registration
├── registerPassenger.html       # Passenger registration
├── bookRide.html                # Ride booking form
├── styles/
│   └── style.css                # Common styles
├── scripts/
│   └── main.js / auth.js        # JS logic for login/register/booking
├── screenshots/
│   └── *.png                    # UI snapshots for documentation
└── README.md

